# Frontend architecture (feature-based)

## Where files go

- `resources/js/features/<domain>/` — all domain code (components + a co-located `types.ts`). Domains: `dossiers`, `document-requests`, `portal`, `questionnaires`, `clients`, `invitations`, `media`, `dashboard`, `workspaces`, `members`, `audit`, `notifications`, `security`, `settings`.
- `resources/js/components/` — only domain-agnostic shared code: `ui/` (shadcn), `app-shell/` (chrome: nav, sidebar, breadcrumbs), `sortable/`, and generic primitives (`heading`, `input-error`, `text-link`, `alert-error`, `password-input`).
- `resources/js/pages/` — thin Inertia entry points only. Pages compose feature components; they hold no reusable logic.
- `resources/js/types/` — only cross-cutting types (`auth`, `navigation`, `ui`). Domain types live in `features/<domain>/types.ts` and are imported directly, never re-exported through `@/types`.

## When to nest inside a feature

- **Feature root** holds `types.ts`, cross-cutting wiring (e.g. registries), and shared helpers used by multiple subfolders.
- **Nest by audience** when code must not import across sides (`staff/` vs `portal/` — already enforced in Biome for document-requests).
- **Nest by concern** when one audience mixes several topics (status vs stage vs show composition).
- **Stay flat** when a feature has few files that already read as one cluster (~≤5 components, one concern). Examples: `audit`, `dashboard`, `media`, `members`, `notifications`, `portal`, `settings`, `workspaces`.
- **No barrel `index.ts` files** — import concrete paths (e.g. `@/features/dossiers/status/dossier-status-badge`).
- **Keep descriptive filenames** inside subfolders (same style as `document-requests/staff/review/document-request-review.tsx`).
- **Do not move `types.ts`** off the feature root.

Current nested layouts:

- `dossiers/` — `permissions/`, `status/`, `stage/`, `show/`, `list/` (includes restore), `create/`, `edit/`, `follow-up/`
- `document-requests/` — `status/`, `staff/builder/`, `staff/review/`, `portal/` (registry + shared upload form stay at root)
- `clients/` — `list/` (index + archive), `manage/` (create/edit/archive button)
- `invitations/` — invitation accept/register UI (`types.ts` at root)
- `security/` — `passkeys/`, `two-factor/` (`delete-user.tsx` stays at root)
- `questionnaires/` — `list/`, `show/`

## Import boundaries (enforced by Biome noRestrictedImports)

- Nothing imports from `@/pages/**`.
- `components/**` never imports from `@/features/**`.
- `features/document-requests/staff/**` and `.../portal/**` never import each other. Only the registry at the feature root (`questionnaire-item-type-registry.tsx`) wires both sides.
- `pages/portal/**` (guest magic-link portal) never imports staff-side UI or `components/app-shell`.

Cross-feature imports of another feature's `types.ts` are fine and intentional (e.g. `@/features/dossiers/types` from document-requests).

## Document request types

New questionnaire item types (currently `file` | `text` | `textarea` | `date` | `number` | `boolean`) are added by:

1. Extending `QuestionnaireItemType` in `features/document-requests/types.ts` (mirrors the PHP `QuestionnaireItemType` enum).
2. Adding a registry entry in `questionnaire-item-type-registry.tsx` with a label, a `StaffContent` renderer (`staff/`), and a `PortalContent` renderer (`portal/`). The `satisfies Record<QuestionnaireItemType, ...>` makes TypeScript flag missing entries.

Never branch on `documentRequest.type` inside cards or pages — resolve through the registry.
